cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper describes the development of a Convolutional Neural Network model for image classification of biomedical polymer-based scaffolds. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of neural networks for image classification also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the mention of fibrous structures seen in cortical bone and fibrous shells suggests the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, as these structures may be imaged using various techniques. Finally, the potential for adaptation to complex machine learning problems suggests the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
